        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10103",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=peptolab",
                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Wouldn't this be handled by the Controller's plugin handler instead? Whilst I can see the convenience for this method, it's not strictly the Controller's job to handle session shutdowns\/commits.\n\nIt may pay instead to have a pre-made plugin that interacts with the Zend_Session component so that it will be trivial to add this to the Controller chain.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=peptolab",
                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-20T18:37:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-20T18:37:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10354",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree, would be best to make this pluggable behavior either via a plugin or on\/off switch.  But I do also agree it is useful to have and simplifies the process.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-09T00:22:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-09T00:22:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11244",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The issue is that Zend_Controller_Action::_redirect() actually calls exit() as its last argument, meaning that no plugins are then called.\n\nA simple check for $_SESSION can determine if the session is started, and then a session_write_close() prior to the header will fixate it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-09T14:57:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-09T14:57:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11245",
                    "author": {
